Package us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D

Class Point2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.Point2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clearable, EpsilonComparable<Point2D>, GeometricallyComparable<Point2D>, GeometryObject<Point2D>, Settable<Point2D>, Transformable, Point2DBasics, Point2DReadOnly, Tuple2DBasics, Tuple2DReadOnly
    public class Point2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements Point2DBasics, GeometryObject<Point2D>
    A 2D point represents the 2D coordinates of a location on the XY-plane.

    This version of 2D point uses double precision fields to save the value of each component. It is meant for garbage free usage.

    Author:
    Sylvain Bertrand

      • geometricallyEquals

        public boolean geometricallyEquals​(Point2D other,
                                   double epsilon)
        Tests if this and other represent the same point 2D to an epsilon.

        Two points are considered geometrically equal if they are at a distance of less than or equal to epsilon.

        Note that this.geometricallyEquals(other, epsilon) == true does not necessarily imply this.epsilonEquals(other, epsilon) and vice versa.

        Specified by:
        geometricallyEquals in interface GeometricallyComparable<Point2D>
        Parameters:
        other - the other point 2D to compare against this. Not modified.
        epsilon - the maximum distance that the two points can be spaced and still considered equal.
        Returns:
        true if the two points represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
